Ecological remarks. This species, both adults and nymphs, was collected at 60 m depth from the exit of the cave of the San Blas stream source (
Fig. 5
), an unusual habitat for a stonefly. The abiotic characteristics were: 67 % humidity, 7 ºC water temperature, 9 ºC air temperature, total absence of light, clear oligotrophic water, and substrate composed mainly by cobble and gravel, but also of sand and lime precipitate.
